               <p>Q. What relation are you to Joseph Shaw? - His wife; he lives in <placeName id="t17950701-52-crimeloc264">St. Martin's Le Grand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17950701-52-crimeloc264" type="placeName" value="St. Martin's Le Grand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17950701-52-crimeloc264" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950701-52-off262 t17950701-52-crimeloc264"></join>. In about half an hour we missed three pots, and I suspected the prisoner, and I catched this one on her half way down the stairs where the pots stood; the pots were in the house on the stairs; I forced it from her; she would not come up at first, but I forced her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I was drinking with my brother, and the smoaking tobacco overcame me, and I took the pot and went down the cellar to get a little water.</p>
